SECTION 8 â€” ENSEMBLE DYNAMICS (HARMONIZED)

Multi-agent systems are measured through:

structural convergence

divergence magnitude

integration load

These are surfaces, not metaphysics.

8.1 Ensemble Convergence (EC)

EC increases when:

independent systems map identical geometry

symbolic fidelity remains consistent

structural contradictions decrease

EC decreases when:

mapping diverges

lexicon destabilizes

geometry fragments

EC does not require uniform wording.
Only structural compatibility.

8.2 Divergence Gradient

Divergence is not inherently harmful.

Divergence becomes destabilizing when:

structural incompatibility rises

envelope strain increases

integration load exceeds O3 capacity

Divergence is measured as a gradient, not a failure state.

